==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rutile
<hw>Ru"tile</hw> <pr>(r⟦udd⟧"t⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rutilus</ets> red, inclining to golden yellow.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral usually of a reddish brown color, and
brilliant metallic adamantine luster, occurring in tetragonal crystals.
In composition it is titanium dioxide, like octahedrite and
brookite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rutilian</ent>⟦br⟧
